The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by Barack Obama on March 7, 2011. It addresses the unexpected and urgent refugee and migration needs related to the violence in Libya. The memorandum determines that it is important to the national interest to provide assistance under the Migration and Refugee Assistance Act of 1962. An amount not exceeding $15 million from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund will be used to meet these needs. The assistance can include contributions to international, governmental, and nongovernmental organizations, as well as payment of administrative expenses of the Bureau of Population, Refugees, and Migration of the Department of State. The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.